10:12.362 --> 10:15.129
We've lived our life
one way for all these years

10:15.231 --> 10:17.899
believing everything the Church
asked us to believe

10:18.001 --> 10:19.467
without too much griping.

10:19.569 --> 10:21.269
And we appreciate that.

10:21.371 --> 10:22.870
We hate the whiners.

10:22.972 --> 10:24.739
I mean, to the extent that we're allowed

10:24.841 --> 10:26.374
to hate any of our flock.

10:26.476 --> 10:28.976
I don't mind all the rules.

10:29.045 --> 10:31.245
You know, it's been great
not having to think too hard

10:31.347 --> 10:34.615
about stuff... just letting
life wash over me.

10:34.717 --> 10:39.687
But now my wife has been
bringing up questions.

10:39.789 --> 10:41.255
Oof, sounds rough.

10:41.357 --> 10:44.258
You're selling me on celibacy
all over again.

11:15.492 --> 11:18.192
- The eagle has landed.
- There's an eagle?

11:18.294 --> 11:19.727
He put the microphone in her purse.

11:19.829 --> 11:21.295
- Then just say that.
- Are you hungry?

11:21.397 --> 11:22.830
Why are you being so mean to me?

11:22.932 --> 11:24.365
You know what? I did skip lunch.

11:24.467 --> 11:25.733
Shh!

11:25.835 --> 11:28.002
- What's she's saying?
- All I'm hearing is static.

11:28.104 --> 11:29.337
Wait.

11:29.439 --> 11:32.507
Someone's talking about the Dodgers.

11:32.609 --> 11:35.143
They're down 4 to 3 in the 7th.

11:35.245 --> 11:38.479
It just feels like abstinence
isn't realistic for us.

11:38.581 --> 11:41.149
The man, God bless him,
can't get enough of me.

11:41.251 --> 11:42.984
I want to be a good Catholic,
but after eight kids,

11:43.086 --> 11:44.852
it seems like the Church
owes me some wiggle-room.

11:44.954 --> 11:46.554
Uh-huh. I feel like I'm not being heard.

11:46.656 --> 11:48.422
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

11:48.525 --> 11:50.191
How about a few more options?

11:50.293 --> 11:51.759
I mean, is there anything else
the Church is okay with

11:51.861 --> 11:53.261
to help us not have kids?

11:53.363 --> 11:55.029
- Yes!
- Oh, great.

11:55.131 --> 11:57.064
- What is it?
- Oh, uh,

11:57.167 --> 11:59.667
say four Hail Marys and one Our Father.

11:59.769 --> 12:01.169
Well, if that worked,
we wouldn't have Eddie.

12:01.271 --> 12:02.703
- Amazing!
- What?!

12:02.805 --> 12:04.338
Buckner just hit one out!

12:09.179 --> 12:10.611
Why, Peggy!

12:10.713 --> 12:11.879
Oh. Hi, Helen.

12:11.981 --> 12:13.714
- Hi.
- Pretty flowers.

12:13.816 --> 12:15.216
- Yes, they're from my garden.
- Mm.

12:15.318 --> 12:18.019
The Altar Ladies and I
just doing our part.

12:18.121 --> 12:19.587
I'm sure God loves your flowers.

12:19.689 --> 12:21.022
I mean, He made them.

12:21.124 --> 12:22.890
You just killed them
and brought them here.

12:22.992 --> 12:25.126
You know, we haven't seen you
at bingo in a long time.

12:25.228 --> 12:26.928
Maybe you should come by Monday night.

12:27.030 --> 12:29.397
Oh, I'm having an operation on Monday.

12:29.499 --> 12:32.266
Nothing serious.
Just a little ovarian cyst.

12:32.368 --> 12:33.568
- Oh.
- Yeah.

12:33.670 --> 12:34.902
Doctor O'Brien?

12:35.004 --> 12:37.238
- No, Shaff. Why?
- Oh.

12:37.340 --> 12:39.574
Well, perhaps I shouldn't say anything,

12:39.676 --> 12:43.144
but Doctor O'Brien is
a Catholic and a very dear man.

12:43.246 --> 12:44.979
I don't think there will be
much time for small talk.

12:45.081 --> 12:46.747
I'm hoping to be zonked out.

12:46.849 --> 12:48.983
Well, no, what I mean
is if Doctor O'Brien

12:49.085 --> 12:52.119
does the operation,
he can do it in a bigger way

12:52.222 --> 12:56.224
so that a cyst or anything else
can't grow down there.

12:56.326 --> 12:58.626
It's a kindness he does
for Catholic women

12:58.728 --> 13:01.429
who have been blessed with more
than their share of blessings.

13:01.531 --> 13:03.622
Isn't that considered "family planning"?

13:03.647 --> 13:04.676
How could it be?

13:04.701 --> 13:06.500
You're having a necessary operation,

13:06.603 --> 13:08.169
the scope of which is up to the doctor

13:08.271 --> 13:09.837
who uses his best judgment.

13:09.939 --> 13:12.740
That sounds pretty scientific
for the Catholic Church.

13:12.842 --> 13:15.009
Are you sure the Church
is okay with this?

13:15.111 --> 13:17.612
Bonnie Burns actually
spoke to the Bishop

13:17.714 --> 13:19.680
before getting hers, just to be sure.

13:19.782 --> 13:21.482
- Bonnie did this?
- Yes!

13:21.584 --> 13:23.985
All I heard her say is that it's
something Catholic couples do

13:24.087 --> 13:25.353
that Mom thinks is wrong.

13:25.455 --> 13:26.921
And her friend Bonnie Burns did it.

13:27.023 --> 13:28.322
Oh, my God.

13:28.424 --> 13:30.758
That's easy. It's divorce.

13:30.860 --> 13:32.493
- What?
- Absolutely.

13:32.595 --> 13:34.662
Mrs. Burns is that tasty divorcée.

13:34.764 --> 13:36.364
The one who wears hot pants to mass.

13:36.466 --> 13:38.833
She's the reason I sometimes
can't stand up for communion.

13:38.935 --> 13:40.635
Mom and Dad are getting a divorce?

13:40.737 --> 13:43.004
It's the '70s.
Divorce is the new reality.

13:43.106 --> 13:44.772
I don't want them getting a divorce.

13:44.874 --> 13:47.341
The important thing is now
they can compete for our love

13:47.443 --> 13:48.809
instead of the other way around.

13:48.911 --> 13:51.145
Two birthdays, two Christmases.

13:51.247 --> 13:53.014
Maybe a Hanukkah.

13:53.116 --> 13:55.981
I'm picturing Mom ending up with
Mr. Cohen from the dry cleaners.

13:59.278 --> 14:00.367
Now, all things considered,

14:00.422 --> 14:01.850
I think the Doctor O'Brien version

14:01.875 --> 14:03.266
of the surgery is the way to go.

14:03.321 --> 14:05.555
I can't even believe we're
having this conversation.

14:06.235 --> 14:07.863
Look, you're talking about
letting them take out stuff

14:07.930 --> 14:09.262
they don't have to.

14:09.332 --> 14:11.739
It's barbaric,
and it probably costs extra.

14:11.841 --> 14:13.040
But then we'd be done, Mike.

14:13.142 --> 14:14.775
And we could keep our life
the way it is,

14:14.877 --> 14:17.345
with no "black-out days,"
so we don't have to suffer.

14:17.447 --> 14:18.980
But that's what makes it so sketchy.

14:19.082 --> 14:20.548
You do something fun,

14:20.616 --> 14:22.149
you're supposed to get hit
with a little suffering.

14:22.251 --> 14:24.018
That's the deal. Jesus knew.

14:24.087 --> 14:27.722
He had a nice dinner with his
friends, and the next day, that.

14:27.824 --> 14:29.623
Oh, I told you,
Helen and Bonnie looked into it.

14:29.692 --> 14:31.592
- They say it's fine.
- Helen is a degenerate

14:31.694 --> 14:32.760
with a serious bingo problem,

14:32.829 --> 14:34.562
and Bonnie wore a halter top
to a christening,

14:34.664 --> 14:35.930
so please forgive me
if I don't look to them

14:36.032 --> 14:37.665
- for moral guidance.
- The Bishop himself

14:37.767 --> 14:39.800
- gave Bonnie the thumbs-up.
- Yeah, and I bet she wore that

14:39.902 --> 14:41.836
- halter top when she asked him.
- That halter top really made

14:41.938 --> 14:44.171
- a big impression on you, didn't it?
- It was a christening.

14:44.273 --> 14:46.407
It made it very hard for
the baby to concentrate.

14:46.509 --> 14:48.676
Look, I am struggling
with this stuff, too.

14:48.745 --> 14:50.878
I even prayed on it.

14:50.980 --> 14:53.381
Maybe I need to go back and talk
to Father Dunne some more.

14:53.449 --> 14:55.750
Sure. You and the priest
and the bishop and the doctor...

14:55.852 --> 14:57.485
all these men...
get to have big opinions

14:57.553 --> 14:59.153
about whether or not I have another kid.

14:59.255 --> 15:00.721
No one seems to care what I want!

15:00.823 --> 15:03.557
The only person who's really tried
to support me in this is Helen!

15:03.659 --> 15:05.259
And I don't even like her.

15:09.866 --> 15:11.899
- Can you hear anything?
- More arguing,

15:12.001 --> 15:14.001
but Mom walked out, so we missed it.

15:17.006 --> 15:18.272
Peg.

15:18.374 --> 15:19.507
I hear crying.

15:19.609 --> 15:20.908
Is it Dad or the baby?

15:21.010 --> 15:22.276
Just the baby so far.

15:27.216 --> 15:29.283
<i>Dad's instinct was always
that he should take the lead</i>

15:29.385 --> 15:31.185
<i>in all important family decisions.</i>

15:31.254 --> 15:32.748
- I can handle it.
- It's okay.

15:32.803 --> 15:34.537
Go watch TV or something.
I'll do what I do.

15:34.639 --> 15:36.105
<i>It started to dawn on Dad, however,</i>

15:36.174 --> 15:37.673
<i>that each child they added to the family</i>

15:37.775 --> 15:39.608
<i>meant more responsibility and more work.</i>

15:39.710 --> 15:43.212
<i>And not really for him, but for Mom.</i>

15:43.314 --> 15:44.547
Now Mom's back.

15:44.615 --> 15:46.315
She just took Andy away from Dad, and...

15:46.417 --> 15:48.350
Oh, he just spit on her.

15:48.419 --> 15:50.920
Dad spit on her? Divorce gets ugly.

15:51.022 --> 15:52.121
Sounds like he stopped crying.

15:52.223 --> 15:53.455
Mom put him down in the crib.

15:53.558 --> 15:55.291
Now she's going to the dresser.

15:55.393 --> 15:56.458
She's pulling something out.

15:59.730 --> 16:00.729
She's undressing.

16:00.831 --> 16:02.097
Pull me up! Pull me up! Pull me up!

16:02.200 --> 16:03.899
Pull me up!

16:04.001 --> 16:05.701
A divorce? That's your new theory?

16:05.770 --> 16:08.070
Oh, maybe the baby they were
having earlier today

16:08.172 --> 16:09.838
was them trying to save their marriage.

16:09.907 --> 16:11.707
There's evidence, okay? The arguing,

16:11.809 --> 16:14.743
her going away, her talking
about breaking Church rules.

16:14.845 --> 16:17.780
Face it. We're gonna be
children of a broken home.

16:17.882 --> 16:20.716
- I bet I could get a mini bike out of this.
- I blame Dad.

16:20.818 --> 16:22.151
The way she slaves around here

16:22.253 --> 16:24.286
with no appreciation from anyone but me.

16:24.388 --> 16:26.622
To be fair, Mom's not exactly
a day in the park.

16:26.691 --> 16:27.890
You shut your mouth.

16:27.992 --> 16:29.391
She's a day in the park in spring.

16:29.493 --> 16:31.360
Okay, a lot of issues here.

16:31.429 --> 16:33.629
- Some more disturbing than others.
- Yeah! Really!?

16:33.731 --> 16:34.897
Mom and Dad are splitting up!

16:34.999 --> 16:36.365
We don't know that for sure.

16:36.467 --> 16:37.700
- I just listed all...
- Guys! Guys!

16:37.802 --> 16:39.268
There's an obvious way to find out.

16:39.337 --> 16:41.170
Ah, yes, by breaking into divorce court

16:41.272 --> 16:43.072
and rifling through the files.
We'll have to steal a lamp

16:43.174 --> 16:44.573
or something to make it look
like a burglary,

16:44.675 --> 16:45.808
but once we get our hands...

16:45.910 --> 16:48.644
Or we could just ask Mom and Dad.

16:48.713 --> 16:51.914
Honest, regular talking without
any subterfuge or spying.

16:53.284 --> 16:54.917
I-I don't understand.

16:55.019 --> 16:56.852
How are you not in jail yet?

16:56.921 --> 16:58.954
I can pass any lie detector test.

17:01.058 --> 17:02.424
<i>That didn't work, did it?</i>

17:02.526 --> 17:03.525
<i>Maybe next time.</i>

17:03.628 --> 17:05.928
We need to have a family meeting.

17:06.030 --> 17:08.230
About what?
Where I'm gonna bury your body?

17:08.332 --> 17:09.462
I was watching that.

17:09.486 --> 17:11.201
They just want to know
what's happening around here.

17:11.202 --> 17:12.935
I just want to know what's
happening on "Banacek."

17:13.037 --> 17:14.936
They've been hearing a lot
of whispering and arguing.

17:15.039 --> 17:16.739
Are you and Mom talking about divorce?

17:16.840 --> 17:18.906
I wouldn't talk to your father
about divorce.

17:19.010 --> 17:21.310
I'd just hightail it to Tijuana
and send him the papers.

17:21.412 --> 17:23.612
Very sensible. That's why I married you.

17:23.714 --> 17:25.047
I'm going to Tijuana with Mom.

17:25.148 --> 17:27.282
- I want to live with Dad.
- Who invited you?

17:27.385 --> 17:28.851
- Mom?
- Eh...

17:28.953 --> 17:30.719
Let's all calm down.
There's no point in taking sides

17:30.788 --> 17:32.121
- when we don't even know...
- I choose Dad!

17:32.223 --> 17:33.789
I want Mom!
Mostly because of her spaghetti.

17:33.891 --> 17:35.257
Nobody likes a suck-up.

17:35.359 --> 17:36.859
But you will be getting
an extra meatball.

17:36.961 --> 17:38.494
- Yes!
- Let me just say

17:38.562 --> 17:40.462
I completely support this life decision

17:40.564 --> 17:43.632
and will be happy to divide my
time between the both of you.

17:43.734 --> 17:46.435
Also, my love can be purchased
for the price of one mini bike.

17:46.537 --> 17:49.438
I just want to be clear that in
the event of a divorce,

17:49.540 --> 17:51.407
- I don't want any of you.
- You're not sticking them with me.

17:51.509 --> 17:53.575
First thing I'd do is dump
all of you at juvie hall,

17:53.678 --> 17:56.845
get myself a bachelor pad like Banacek.

17:56.947 --> 17:58.380
- Can I come?
- Absolutely.

17:58.482 --> 18:00.549
Look, I don't know where
you clowns got this crap,

18:00.651 --> 18:02.141
but your mother and I are not
getting any divorces.

18:02.165 --> 18:03.155
Honestly.

18:03.180 --> 18:05.345
- Really?
- If we did, it's important to know

18:05.423 --> 18:07.690
that it would be entirely your fault.

18:07.792 --> 18:10.659
- You mean us kids?
- No, you specifically.

18:11.996 --> 18:14.229
He's kidding.

18:14.332 --> 18:16.131
You'd all be to blame.

18:16.233 --> 18:18.067
Your father and I were blissfully happy

18:18.169 --> 18:20.502
before you animals came along,
and we won't let you beat us.

18:20.604 --> 18:23.038
No way. We are Catholics.

18:23.140 --> 18:24.640
We hang in until the bitter end.

18:24.742 --> 18:26.208
Until one of us stands
over the other one

18:26.310 --> 18:28.043
and watches them die.

18:28.145 --> 18:30.179
Oh, honey, so romantic.

18:30.281 --> 18:31.947
I mean it, Peg.

18:32.049 --> 18:34.983
Well, maybe we can avoid
any confusion in the future

18:35.086 --> 18:37.086
if you guys were a little bit
more open with us.

18:37.188 --> 18:38.487
Okay.

18:38.556 --> 18:42.091
Well, maybe there is
one thing you should know.

18:42.193 --> 18:44.660
I'm gonna be having
an operation on Monday.

18:44.762 --> 18:45.661
What?

18:45.763 --> 18:46.962
I'm gonna be fine.

18:47.064 --> 18:48.297
I'm gonna be gone for three days,

18:48.399 --> 18:49.798
and then I'm coming back.

18:49.900 --> 18:52.000
As tempting as the sweet
rest of death might be.

18:52.103 --> 18:54.002
What about all the arguing we heard?

18:54.105 --> 18:56.505
Oh, you know how your mom gets...

18:56.607 --> 18:59.408
when I'm being pig-headed.

18:59.510 --> 19:01.744
There was this important
decision we were trying to make

19:01.846 --> 19:06.615
that... well, it turns out is
mostly not my decision at all.

19:06.717 --> 19:08.951
It's hers.

19:09.053 --> 19:12.154
I was wrong, but your mom
forgives me, right?

19:13.524 --> 19:15.090
Yes, I do.

19:16.927 --> 19:20.129
See, no divorce.

19:20.231 --> 19:23.799
Turn on "Banacek" and get out.

19:23.901 --> 19:25.601
<i>This was a big deal...</i>

19:25.703 --> 19:27.636
<i>my mom and dad opening up
with personal details</i>

19:27.738 --> 19:29.304
<i>and feelings like never before...</i>

19:29.407 --> 19:31.974
Um, so, the surgery you're having.

19:32.076 --> 19:34.443
- What kind of operation is it?
- Well, funny you should ask.

19:34.545 --> 19:35.844
It's a None-Of-Your-Business-ectomy.

19:35.946 --> 19:37.012
Now, beat it!

19:37.114 --> 19:38.647
<i>And then, right back to normal.</i>

19:42.610 --> 19:43.930
Weirdos.

19:44.916 --> 19:47.087
- Mommy?
- Yeah, Pat?

19:47.173 --> 19:50.329
I've been thinking a lot
about my new baby sister.

19:50.423 --> 19:52.423
- Baby sister?
- I named her Kathy.

19:52.492 --> 19:54.177
It's a lot better name than Buffy.

19:54.240 --> 19:55.760
Neither one is great.

19:55.862 --> 19:57.361
But listen,

19:57.430 --> 19:59.530
I don't know if you'll be
getting a baby sister, Pat.

19:59.599 --> 20:01.599
But I really, really want one.

20:01.667 --> 20:04.034
See, I already got Kathy a present.

20:04.137 --> 20:05.236
Pinky Bear.

20:05.338 --> 20:06.637
I want to give her to Kathy

20:06.706 --> 20:08.606
so she won't feel alone
being the only girl.

20:08.708 --> 20:11.675
Aww, that's very generous of you.

20:11.778 --> 20:15.513
If Kathy does show up one day,
I'll see that she gets this.

20:15.615 --> 20:17.148
Thanks, Mom.

20:20.286 --> 20:21.485
You ready for bed?

20:21.587 --> 20:23.187
Yeah.

20:23.289 --> 20:28.225
And, um, I've made a decision
about the operation on Monday.

20:29.462 --> 20:32.029
Okay.

20:32.131 --> 20:33.497
Good.

20:35.601 --> 20:37.034
What are you doing with Pat's bear?

20:37.136 --> 20:38.869
Oh, I've been trying to get this

20:38.971 --> 20:40.882
grimy thing away from him for months.

